        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Equations in data-box.</text> To edit the data-value of a parameter, you can enter an equation: Degrees are in <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Radians</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">E.g: Sin(1) <equation><![CDATA[\cong]]></equation> 0.8415</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">If you need to enter a value for <equation font-size="24" color="#000000"><![CDATA[\pi]]></equation>, you can enter:</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">3.14 - 2dp Note: <text styleclass="VariableName-small">22/7</text>&#32;<equation><![CDATA[\cong]]></equation> 3.143</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">3.14159 - 5dp. Note: <text styleclass="VariableName-small">355/113 </text><equation styleclass="VariableName-small"><![CDATA[\cong]]></equation><text styleclass="VariableName-small"> 3.141593... </text>usually good enough</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">3.14159265 - 8dp</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">3.14159265358 - 11dp</para>
